<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE42FF89FF0AFD1E5FE9FC5D" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFD1E5E22FC9D" blockId="2.[166,1225,719,1002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Palaearctic: from 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FDA1FD015E83FD5E" box="[624,709,719,745]" name="Ireland" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Ireland</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD3FFD015F74FD5E" box="[750,818,719,745]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FCEEFD1E5FD4FD5D" box="[831,914,720,746]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">France</collectingCountry>
, European parts of 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FBACFD01588FFD5E" box="[1149,1225,719,745]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Russia</collectingCountry>
and Georgia. Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FE0CFD215E72FCBE" box="[477,564,751,777]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FDEEFD215EECFCBE" box="[575,682,751,777]" name="Armenia" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Armenia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD65FD215F01FCBE" box="[692,839,751,777]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Azerbaidjan</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FC81FD3E5FC3FCBD" box="[848,901,752,778]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FC5EFD21581EFCBD" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[911,1112,751,778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref6810" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1987. A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Biologia 86. Prirodovedecka Fakulta, Univerzita J. E. Purkyne, Brne, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FBB3FD215E19FC9D" author="Seddighi Sadr, F. &amp; Mohammadzade Namin, S." pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="43 - 45" refId="ref6894" refString="Seddighi Sadr, F., Mohammadzade Namin, S. 2016. The snail killing flies (Diptera, Sciomyzidae) in Gilan Province, with a new record for Iranian fauna. Ukrainska Entomofaunistyka, 7 (1), 43 - 45." type="journal article" year="2016">Seddighi Sadr, Mohammadzade Namin (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFCE15FE9FC5D" blockId="2.[166,1225,719,1002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
Biology. Based on Knutson (1973) laboratory studies; larvae are predator of a range of terrestrial snails (
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FE75FC815EC5FCDE" baseAuthorityName="O. F. Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[420,643,847,873]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlicopidae" genus="Cochlicopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lubrica">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FE75FC815EC5FCDE" box="[420,643,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Cochlicopa lubrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FD47FC9E5F5FFCDE" authorityName="Siemaschko" authorityYear="1847" box="[662,793,848,874]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cochlicopidae" genus="Cochlicopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FD47FC9E5F5FFCDE" box="[662,793,848,874]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">C. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FCFCFC9E5841FCDE" baseAuthorityName="O. F. Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[813,1031,847,873]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discidae" genus="Discus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rotundatus">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FCFCFC9E5841FCDE" box="[813,1031,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Discus rotundatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FBCAFC815F23FC3E" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FBCAFC815882FCDE" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1051,1220,847,873]" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Helicella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="itala">Helicella itala</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FF77FCBE5D77FC3E" authorityName="Montagu" authorityYear="1803" box="[166,305,880,905]" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Helicella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="caperata">H. caperata</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FEEFFCBE5E52FC3E" authority=", Eulota" authorityName="Eulota" box="[318,532,879,905]" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Cernuella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="virgata">H. virgata, Eulota</taxonomicName>
fruticum, 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FD43FCBE5F23FC3E" authorityName="Vala" authorityYear="1989" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[658,869,879,905]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hygromiidae" genus="Hygromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hispida">Hygromia hispida</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FC75FCA1580BFC3D" box="[932,1101,879,906]" class="Gastropoda" family="Oxychilidae" genus="Oxychilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FC75FCA15851FC3E" box="[932,1047,879,905]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Oxychilus</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
), then became saprophagous on dead snail host. Knutson (1973) described all larval stages and stated that puparium is formed outside the host snail, and represents the overwintering stage. This species is strictly univoltine (Knutson, 1973; 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FD3AFC015FE5FC5D" author="Gaponov, S. P." box="[747,931,975,1002]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="54 - 63" refId="ref6197" refString="Gaponov, S. P. 2016. Fauna and bioecology of snail-killing flies (Diptera: Sciomyzidae) in the central black soil region of Russia. Proceedings of Voronezh State University. Ser.: Chemistry. Biology. Pharmacy, 1, 54 - 63." type="journal article" year="2016">Gaponov, 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
